LOIRE VALLEY WHITE

The Loire River meanders at its own delicious slow pace for 600 miles through France and empties into the Atlantic at Nantes. Along its banks, you can discover some of the best wine values of the world. The Gros Plant will delight you, the Muscadet will bring joy to your warm weather living, and the Sancerre, and Pouilly-Blanc-Fumé will provide depth of flavor, beautiful bouquet and sheer delight—all at a liveable price.
